<paragraph blockId="46.[144,758,1603,1687]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authority="Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[373,481,1634,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[373,481,1634,1656]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, Latin for beauty, refers to the attractive dorsal markings and colouration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
